# ISSUE: Element won't center

Symptoms:
- `margin: auto` not working
- Flexbox centering not working
- Element stuck to left/top

## Quick Fixes

### 1. Horizontal centering (block element):
```css
/* Element needs a width */
.center-me {
  width: 200px;        /* or max-width */
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}
```

### 2. Horizontal centering (inline/text):
```css
.parent {
  text-align: center;
}
```

### 3. Flexbox (horizontal + vertical):
```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;  /* horizontal */
  align-items: center;      /* vertical */
  height: 100vh;            /* parent needs height! */
}
```

### 4. Grid (easiest):
```css
.parent {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

### 5. Absolute positioning:
```css
.parent {
  position: relative;
}

.child {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
```

## Common Mistakes

### Forgot parent height:
```css
/* Won't work - parent has no height */
.parent {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

/* Fixed - parent has height */
.parent {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;  /* or min-height */
}
```

### Block element without width:
```css
/* margin:auto needs width to work */
.block {
  margin: 0 auto;
  /* Missing width - takes 100%, nothing to center */
}
```

### Using wrong flex direction:
```css
/* justify-content is MAIN axis */
/* align-items is CROSS axis */

/* Row (default): main=horizontal, cross=vertical */
flex-direction: row;
justify-content: center;  /* horizontal */
align-items: center;      /* vertical */

/* Column: main=vertical, cross=horizontal */
flex-direction: column;
justify-content: center;  /* vertical */
align-items: center;      /* horizontal */
```

## Modern One-Liner
```css
.center-anything {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
}
```

## Related Issues
- Element overflowing container
- Flexbox items not wrapping
- Grid items not sizing correctly

