// Cause 3: Default vs named
// If module uses default export:
// module.js: export default { foo, bar };

// Wrong:
import { foo } from './module';

// Right:
import module from './module';
const { foo } = module;

// Or if using named exports:
// module.js: export { foo, bar };
import { foo } from './module';  // Works
```

**Prevention:**
- Check module documentation for export style
- Use TypeScript for export validation
- Use IDE auto-import

