## Warning: Each child should have unique "key" prop

**Symptoms:**
- Console warning about keys
- List items re-render unnecessarily
- Input focus lost when typing

**Causes:**
1. **Missing key prop** - No key on mapped elements
2. **Index as key** - Causes issues with reordering
3. **Duplicate keys** - Same key used twice

**Solutions:**

```javascript
// Cause 1: Add unique key
// Wrong:
{items.map(item => (
  <ListItem>{item.name}</ListItem>
))}

// Right:
{items.map(item => (
  <ListItem key={item.id}>{item.name}</ListItem>
))}

// Cause 2: Don't use index for dynamic lists
// Bad (if list can reorder/filter):
{items.map((item, index) => (
  <ListItem key={index}>{item.name}</ListItem>
))}

// Good (stable identifier):
{items.map(item => (
  <ListItem key={item.id}>{item.name}</ListItem>
))}

// Index is OK for:
// - Static lists that never change
// - Items without stable IDs
// - Lists that never reorder

// Cause 3: Ensure unique keys
// Check for duplicate IDs in data
const uniqueItems = items.filter(
  (item, index, arr) => arr.findIndex(i => i.id === item.id) === index
);

// Or generate keys:
import { nanoid } from 'nanoid';
const itemsWithKeys = items.map(item => ({
  ...item,
  _key: item.id || nanoid()
}));
```

**Prevention:**
- Always use stable, unique identifiers as keys
- Generate IDs when creating data, not during render
- Never use random values as keys (changes every render)

