## UnhandledPromiseRejection / Uncaught Exception

**Symptoms:**
- `UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning` (Node.js warning)
- Process crashes unexpectedly
- Node.js 15+ exits on unhandled rejection

**Solutions:**

```javascript
// Global handlers (monitoring, not recovery)
process.on('uncaughtException', (err, origin) => {
  console.error('Uncaught Exception:', err);
  console.error('Origin:', origin);
  // Log to monitoring service
  // Then exit - state may be corrupted
  process.exit(1);
});

process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason, promise) => {
  console.error('Unhandled Rejection at:', promise);
  console.error('Reason:', reason);
  // In Node 15+, this will exit by default
});

// Better: Always handle promise rejections
async function main() {
  try {
    await riskyOperation();
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Operation failed:', err);
    // Handle gracefully
  }
}

// Express error middleware
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Something went wrong' });
});
```

**Prevention:**
- Always add .catch() to promises
- Use try/catch with async/await
- Add Express error middleware
- Use process managers (PM2) for restart on crash

