# tsconfig.json Common Mistakes

## The Pain

TypeScript config issues cause cryptic errors, broken builds, and "works on my machine" problems. Here's how to avoid the common pitfalls.

## Mistake #1: Not Using strict Mode

```json
// ❌ Too permissive - defeats the purpose of TypeScript
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": false
  }
}

// ✅ Enable strict mode
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true
  }
}
```

**What `strict: true` enables:**
- `strictNullChecks` - Catch null/undefined errors
- `strictFunctionTypes` - Proper function type checking
- `strictBindCallApply` - Typed bind/call/apply
- `strictPropertyInitialization` - Class property checks
- `noImplicitAny` - No implicit any types
- `noImplicitThis` - No implicit this
- `alwaysStrict` - Emit "use strict"

**If migrating gradually:**
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": false,
    "strictNullChecks": true,  // Enable one at a time
    "noImplicitAny": true
  }
}
```

## Mistake #2: Wrong module/moduleResolution Combo

```json
// ❌ Mismatched settings cause import issues
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "node"  // Won't find .js extensions!
  }
}

// ✅ Modern bundler setup (Vite, webpack, esbuild)
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler"
  }
}

// ✅ Node.js with ESM
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "module": "NodeNext",
    "moduleResolution": "NodeNext"
  }
}

// ✅ Node.js with CommonJS
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "module": "CommonJS",
    "moduleResolution": "node"
  }
}
```

## Mistake #3: Forgetting esModuleInterop

```typescript
// ❌ Without esModuleInterop, default imports break
import express from 'express';  // Error!

// You'd have to write:
import * as express from 'express';
```

```json
// ✅ Enable it
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true  // For type checking only
  }
}
```

## Mistake #4: outDir Without rootDir

```json
// ❌ Unpredictable output structure
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist"
    // rootDir not set - TypeScript guesses
  }
}

// ✅ Be explicit
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "outDir": "./dist"
  }
}
```

**The difference:**
```
Project structure:
  src/
    index.ts
    utils/
      helper.ts

Without rootDir: dist/src/index.js (extra nesting!)
With rootDir:    dist/index.js (flat, as expected)
```

## Mistake #5: include/exclude Conflicts

```json
// ❌ Tests compiled into production build
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist"
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*"]  // This includes test files in src!
}

// ✅ Exclude tests
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist"
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*"],
  "exclude": ["**/*.test.ts", "**/*.spec.ts", "node_modules"]
}

// ✅ Better: Separate configs for build vs test
// tsconfig.json (base)
// tsconfig.build.json (production)
// tsconfig.test.json (testing)
```

## Mistake #6: Not Setting target Appropriately

```json
// ❌ Wrong target for your runtime
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES5"  // Unnecessarily old, larger output
  }
}

// ✅ Match your Node.js version
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2022",  // Node 18+
    "lib": ["ES2022"]
  }
}

// ✅ For browsers, let bundler handle it
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ESNext",  // Bundler will downlevel
    "lib": ["ESNext", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"]
  }
}
```

**Target by Node version:**
- Node 16: ES2021
- Node 18: ES2022
- Node 20+: ES2023

## Mistake #7: Missing lib Entries

```typescript
// ❌ Error: Property 'replaceAll' does not exist on type 'string'
"hello".replaceAll("l", "L");

// ❌ Error: 'fetch' is not defined
fetch("https://api.example.com");
```

```json
// ✅ Add required libs
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "lib": [
      "ES2022",        // Modern JS features
      "DOM",           // Browser APIs
      "DOM.Iterable"   // NodeList iteration
    ]
  }
}
```

## Mistake #8: skipLibCheck Hiding Real Errors

```json
// ❌ Hides errors in your .d.ts files too
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "skipLibCheck": true
  }
}

// ✅ Keep it for faster builds, but check periodically
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "skipLibCheck": true  // Faster, but run without it occasionally
  }
}
```

**When to disable skipLibCheck:**
- When debugging type issues
- Before major releases
- When updating @types packages

## Mistake #9: Broken Path Aliases

```json
// ❌ Incomplete setup
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["src/*"]
    }
    // Missing baseUrl!
  }
}

// ✅ Complete setup
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"],
      "@components/*": ["./src/components/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Remember:** Bundlers need separate config too!

```javascript
// vite.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import path from 'path';

export default defineConfig({
  resolve: {
    alias: {
      '@': path.resolve(__dirname, './src'),
    },
  },
});
```

## Mistake #10: Ignoring Declaration Files

```json
// ❌ Can't use your package as a library
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "declaration": false
  }
}

// ✅ Generate .d.ts files
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "declaration": true,
    "declarationDir": "./dist/types",
    "declarationMap": true  // Source maps for .d.ts
  }
}
```

## Mistake #11: noEmit Confusion

```json
// ❌ Confusing: TypeScript won't output anything
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "noEmit": true  // These contradict each other!
  }
}

// ✅ Use noEmit when a bundler handles output
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "noEmit": true  // Vite/webpack does the building
  }
}

// ✅ Use outDir when TypeScript builds
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "noEmit": false  // Or just omit this
  }
}
```

## Mistake #12: Inconsistent Configs in Monorepo

```json
// ❌ Each package has completely different settings
// packages/a/tsconfig.json
{ "compilerOptions": { "strict": true, "target": "ES2020" } }

// packages/b/tsconfig.json
{ "compilerOptions": { "strict": false, "target": "ES5" } }
```

```json
// ✅ Shared base config
// tsconfig.base.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true,
    "target": "ES2022",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "declaration": true
  }
}

// packages/a/tsconfig.json
{
  "extends": "../../tsconfig.base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src"
  },
  "include": ["src"]
}
```

## Quick Reference: Recommended Configs

### Node.js Library
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2022",
    "module": "NodeNext",
    "moduleResolution": "NodeNext",
    "strict": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "declaration": true,
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src"
  },
  "include": ["src"],
  "exclude": ["**/*.test.ts"]
}
```

### Vite/React App
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ESNext",
    "lib": ["ESNext", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "strict": true,
    "jsx": "react-jsx",
    "noEmit": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["src"]
}
```

### Next.js
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2017",
    "lib": ["DOM", "DOM.Iterable", "ESNext"],
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "strict": true,
    "jsx": "preserve",
    "noEmit": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "incremental": true,
    "plugins": [{ "name": "next" }]
  },
  "include": ["next-env.d.ts", "**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx", ".next/types/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules"]
}
```

## Debugging Config Issues

```bash
# See effective config
npx tsc --showConfig

# Check what files are included
npx tsc --listFiles

# Trace module resolution
npx tsc --traceResolution

# Explain why a file is included
npx tsc --explainFiles
```

