## 📐 Layout Trends

### 1. Bento Grid Layouts
Inspired by Japanese lunch boxes — modular, asymmetric card-based layouts.

```css
.bento-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
  gap: 16px;
}

/* Vary card sizes for emphasis */
.bento-grid .featured {
  grid-column: span 2;
}
```

**Best for:** Portfolios, SaaS dashboards, feature showcases

### 2. Anti-Grid / Organic Layouts
Break free from rigid grids with fluid, biomorphic shapes.

```css
.organic-section {
  border-radius: 40% 60% 70% 30% / 40% 50% 60% 50%;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-calm), var(--accent-warm));
}
```

